## дёҠдёҖйҳ¶ж®өзҡ„и°ғжҹҘз»“жһң

еҹәдәҺеҜ№д»Јз Ғеә“зҡ„ж·ұе…ҘеҲҶжһҗпјҢжҲ‘зҺ°еңЁз”ҹжҲҗе®Ңж•ҙзҡ„жҠҖжңҜжҠҘе‘ҠгҖӮ

---

# NOS ж“ҚдҪңзі»з»ҹеҶ…ж ёжҠҖжңҜеҲҶжһҗжҠҘе‘Ҡ

## 1. еҲҶжһҗжҰӮиҝ°

### 1.1 еҲҶжһҗиҢғеӣҙ
жң¬жҠҘе‘ҠеҜ№ NOSпјҲеҹәдәҺ StarryOS/ArceOS жЎҶжһ¶пјүж“ҚдҪңзі»з»ҹеҶ…ж ёиҝӣиЎҢдәҶе…Ёйқўзҡ„жҠҖжңҜеҲҶжһҗпјҢж¶өзӣ–пјҡ
- йЎ№зӣ®з»“жһ„дёҺжһ„е»әзі»з»ҹ
- ж ёеҝғеӯҗзі»з»ҹе®һзҺ°з»ҶиҠӮ
- д»Јз ҒиҙЁйҮҸдёҺжһ¶жһ„и®ҫи®Ў
- еҠҹиғҪе®Ңж•ҙжҖ§иҜ„дј°

### 1.2 жөӢиҜ•жү§иЎҢжғ…еҶө
**жһ„е»әжөӢиҜ•**пјҡе°қиҜ•еңЁжҸҗдҫӣзҡ„е·Ҙе…·й“ҫзҺҜеўғдёӯжһ„е»әйЎ№зӣ®пјҢйҒҮеҲ°д»ҘдёӢй—®йўҳпјҡ
- йЎ№зӣ®иҰҒжұӮ `nightly-2026-02-25` Rust е·Ҙе…·й“ҫ
- жһ„е»әиҫ…еҠ©е·Ҙе…· `cargo-axplat` зј–иҜ‘еӨұиҙҘпјҢеҺҹеӣ жҳҜиҜҘе·Ҙе…·й“ҫзјәе°‘ `x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu` зӣ®ж Үзҡ„ `std` еә“
- иҝҷжҳҜжһ„е»әзҺҜеўғй…ҚзҪ®й—®йўҳпјҢдёҚеҪұе“ҚеҜ№д»Јз Ғжң¬иә«зҡ„еҲҶжһҗ

**иҝҗиЎҢж—¶жөӢиҜ•**пјҡз”ұдәҺжһ„е»әжңӘиғҪе®ҢжҲҗпјҢжңӘиҝӣиЎҢ QEMU иҝҗиЎҢж—¶жөӢиҜ•гҖӮдҪҶйҖҡиҝҮд»Јз Ғе®ЎжҹҘпјҢзЎ®и®ӨйЎ№зӣ®е…·еӨҮе®Ңж•ҙзҡ„жөӢиҜ•еҹәзЎҖи®ҫж–ҪпјҲLTP жөӢиҜ•жЎҶжһ¶йӣҶжҲҗгҖҒCI жөӢиҜ•и„ҡжң¬пјүгҖӮ

---

## 2. йЎ№зӣ®жһ¶жһ„дёҺз»„з»Ү

### 2.1 д»Јз Ғи§„жЁЎз»ҹи®Ў
- **еҶ…ж ёж ёеҝғд»Јз Ғ**пјҡ26,574 иЎҢ Rust д»Јз ҒпјҲ`src/kernel/src/`пјү
- **зі»з»ҹи°ғз”ЁеҲҶеҸ‘**пјҡ886 иЎҢпјҲ`syscall/mod.rs`пјү
- **з¬¬дёүж–№дҫқиө–**пјҡзәҰ 397 дёӘ crateпјҲvendor зӣ®еҪ•пјү
- **ArceOS з»„д»¶**пјҡзәҰ 50 дёӘж ёеҝғжЁЎеқ—

### 2.2 жЁЎеқ—еұӮж¬Ўз»“жһ„

```
starryos (йЎ¶еұӮ crate)
в”ңв”Җв”Җ starry-kernel (еҶ…ж ёж ёеҝғ)
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ config/          # жһ¶жһ„й…ҚзҪ® (riscv64, loongarch64, aarch64, x86_64)
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ entry.rs         # еҶ…ж ёе…ҘеҸЈдёҺ init иҝӣзЁӢеҗҜеҠЁ
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ mm/              # еҶ…еӯҳз®ЎзҗҶеӯҗзі»з»ҹ
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ task/            # иҝӣзЁӢ/зәҝзЁӢз®ЎзҗҶ
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ file/            # ж–Үд»¶дёҺи®ҫеӨҮжҠҪиұЎ
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ pseudofs/        # дјӘж–Үд»¶зі»з»ҹ
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ syscall/         # зі»з»ҹи°ғз”Ёе®һзҺ°
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ time.rs          # ж—¶й—ҙз®ЎзҗҶе·Ҙе…·
в””в”Җв”Җ init/                # з”ЁжҲ·жҖҒ init зЁӢеәҸ
```

### 2.3 и®ҫи®Ўе“ІеӯҰ
йЎ№зӣ®йҮҮз”Ё**е®ҸеҶ…ж ёпјҲMonolithic Kernelпјү**жһ¶жһ„пјҢеҹәдәҺ ArceOS зҡ„жЁЎеқ—еҢ– unikernel жЎҶжһ¶жһ„е»әгҖӮж ёеҝғи®ҫи®ЎзҗҶеҝөпјҡ
- **Linux е…је®№жҖ§**пјҡзі»з»ҹи°ғз”ЁжҺҘеҸЈдёҺ Linux й«ҳеәҰе…је®№
- **жЁЎеқ—еҢ–з»„з»Ү**пјҡеҗ„еӯҗзі»з»ҹйҖҡиҝҮжё…жҷ°зҡ„жҺҘеҸЈдәӨдә’
- **е®үе…ЁжҖ§дјҳе…Ҳ**пјҡеҲ©з”Ё Rust зҡ„жүҖжңүжқғзі»з»ҹе’Ңзұ»еһӢе®үе…Ёзү№жҖ§
- **еӨҡжһ¶жһ„ж”ҜжҢҒ**пјҡд»Јз ҒйҖҡиҝҮ `cfg_if` е®Ҹж”ҜжҢҒеӨҡз§Қ CPU жһ¶жһ„

---

## 3. еҶ…еӯҳз®ЎзҗҶеӯҗзі»з»ҹ

### 3.1 жһ¶жһ„жҰӮиҝ°
еҶ…еӯҳз®ЎзҗҶеӯҗзі»з»ҹдҪҚдәҺ `src/kernel/src/mm/`пјҢе®һзҺ°дәҶе®Ңж•ҙзҡ„иҷҡжӢҹеҶ…еӯҳз®ЎзҗҶеҠҹиғҪгҖӮ

**ж ёеҝғз»„д»¶**пјҡ
- `AddrSpace`пјҡиҷҡжӢҹең°еқҖз©әй—ҙз®ЎзҗҶ
- `Backend`пјҡеҶ…еӯҳжҳ е°„еҗҺз«ҜпјҲLinearгҖҒCOWгҖҒSharedгҖҒFileпјү
- `loader.rs`пјҡELF еҠ иҪҪеҷЁ
- `access.rs`пјҡз”ЁжҲ·з©әй—ҙеҶ…еӯҳи®ҝй—®йӘҢиҜҒ

### 3.2 ең°еқҖз©әй—ҙз®ЎзҗҶ

#### 3.2.1 ең°еқҖз©әй—ҙз»“жһ„
```rust
pub struct AddrSpace {
    va_range: VirtAddrRange,      // иҷҡжӢҹең°еқҖиҢғеӣҙ
    areas: MemorySet<Backend>,    // еҶ…еӯҳеҢәеҹҹйӣҶеҗҲ
    pt: PageTable,                // йЎөиЎЁ
}
```

**RISC-V 64 ең°еқҖеёғеұҖ**пјҲ`config/riscv64.rs`пјүпјҡ
```rust
pub const USER_SPACE_BASE: usize = 0x1000;
pub const USER_SPACE_SIZE: usize = 0x3f_ffff_f000;  // ~256GB
pub const USER_STACK_TOP: usize = 0x4_0000_0000;
pub const USER_STACK_SIZE: usize = 0x800_000;       // 8MB
pub const USER_HEAP_BASE: usize = 0x4000_0000;
pub const USER_HEAP_SIZE_MAX: usize = 0x2000_0000;  // 512MB
pub const SIGNAL_TRAMPOLINE: usize = 0x6000_1000;
```

#### 3.2.2 е…ій”®ж“ҚдҪңе®һзҺ°

**еҶ…еӯҳжҳ е°„**пјҲ`aspace/mod.rs`пјүпјҡ
```rust
pub fn map(
    &mut self,
    start: VirtAddr,
    size: usize,
    flags: MappingFlags,
    populate: bool,
    backend: Backend,
) -> AxResult {
    self.validate_region(start, size)?;
    let area = MemoryArea::new(start, size, flags, backend);
    self.areas.map(area, &mut self.pt, false)?;
    if populate {
        self.populate_area(start, size, flags)?;
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

**зјәйЎөеӨ„зҗҶ**пјҲ`access.rs`пјүпјҡ
```rust
#[register_trap_handler(PAGE_FAULT)]
fn handle_page_fault(vaddr: VirtAddr, access_flags: MappingFlags) -> bool {
    let curr = current();
    let Some(thr) = curr.try_as_thread() else {
        return false;
    };
    if unlikely(!thr.is_accessing_user_memory()) {
        return false;
    }
    thr.proc_data
        .aspace
        .lock()
        .handle_page_fault(vaddr, access_flags)
}
```

### 3.3 жҳ е°„еҗҺз«Ҝе®һзҺ°

#### 3.3.1 Copy-on-Write (COW) еҗҺз«Ҝ
**ж–Үд»¶**пјҡ`aspace/backend/cow.rs`

COW еҗҺз«Ҝе®һзҺ°дәҶеҶҷж—¶еӨҚеҲ¶иҜӯд№үпјҢз”ЁдәҺ `MAP_PRIVATE` жҳ е°„е’Ң `fork()` зі»з»ҹи°ғз”ЁгҖӮ

**ж ёеҝғж•°жҚ®з»“жһ„**пјҡ
```rust
pub struct CowBackend {
    start: VirtAddr,
    size: PageSize,
    file: Option<(FileBackend, u64, Option<u64>)>,
}

struct FrameRefCnt(u16);  // еј•з”Ёи®Ўж•°

static FRAME_TABLE: SpinNoIrq<FrameTableRefCount> = 
    SpinNoIrq::new(FrameTableRefCount::new());
```

**COW зјәйЎөеӨ„зҗҶ**пјҡ
```rust
fn handle_cow_fault(
    &self,
    vaddr: VirtAddr,
    paddr: PhysAddr,
    flags: MappingFlags,
    pt: &mut PageTableCursor,
) -> AxResult {
    let mut frame_table = FRAME_TABLE.lock();
    let frame = frame_table.get_frame_ref(paddr).ok_or(AxError::BadAddress)?;
    drop(frame_table);
    let mut frame = frame.lock();

    match frame.0 {
        1 => {
            // е”ҜдёҖеј•з”ЁпјҢзӣҙжҺҘеҚҮзә§жқғйҷҗ
            pt.protect(vaddr, flags)?;
        }
        _ => {
            // еӨҡеј•з”ЁпјҢйңҖиҰҒеӨҚеҲ¶зү©зҗҶйЎө
            let new_frame = self.alloc_new_frame(false)?;
            unsafe {
                core::ptr::copy_nonoverlapping(
                    phys_to_virt(paddr).as_ptr(),
                    phys_to_virt(new_frame).as_mut_ptr(),
                    self.size as _,
                );
            }
            pt.remap(vaddr, new_frame, flags)?;
            frame.drop_frame(paddr, self.size);
        }
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

**fork ж—¶зҡ„е…ӢйҡҶжҳ е°„**пјҡ
```rust
fn clone_map(
    &self,
    range: VirtAddrRange,
    flags: MappingFlags,
    old_pt: &mut PageTableCursor,
    new_pt: &mut PageTableCursor,
    _new_aspace: &Arc<Mutex<AddrSpace>>,
) -> AxResult<Backend> {
    let cow_flags = flags - MappingFlags::WRITE;  // з§»йҷӨеҶҷжқғйҷҗ

    // жү№йҮҸеўһеҠ еј•з”Ёи®Ўж•°пјҢеҮҸе°‘й”Ғз«һдәү
    let mut entries: Vec<(VirtAddr, PhysAddr, Arc<SpinNoIrq<FrameRefCnt>>)> = Vec::new();
    {
        let mut frame_table = FRAME_TABLE.lock();
        for vaddr in pages_in(range, self.size)? {
            match old_pt.query(vaddr) {
                Ok((paddr, _, page_size)) => {
                    assert_eq!(page_size, self.size);
                    let frame_ref = frame_table.get_frame_ref(paddr)
                        .ok_or(AxError::BadAddress)?;
                    frame_ref.lock().0 += 1;
                    entries.push((vaddr, paddr, frame_ref));
                }
                Err(PagingError::NotMapped) => {}
                Err(_) => return Err(AxError::BadAddress),
            }
        }
    }

    // еңЁж–°йЎөиЎЁдёӯе»әз«ӢеҸӘиҜ»жҳ е°„
    for (vaddr, paddr, _) in entries {
        new_pt.map(vaddr, paddr, self.size, cow_flags)?;
    }

    Ok(Backend::Cow(self.clone()))
}
```

#### 3.3.2 е…ұдә«еҶ…еӯҳеҗҺз«Ҝ
**ж–Үд»¶**пјҡ`aspace/backend/shared.rs`

з”ЁдәҺ System V IPC е…ұдә«еҶ…еӯҳе’Ң `MAP_SHARED | MAP_ANONYMOUS`гҖӮ

```rust
pub struct SharedPages {
    pub phys_pages: Vec<PhysAddr>,
    pub size: PageSize,
}

pub struct SharedBackend {
    start: VirtAddr,
    pages: Arc<SharedPages>,
}

impl BackendOps for SharedBackend {
    fn map(&self, range: VirtAddrRange, flags: MappingFlags, pt: &mut PageTableCursor) -> AxResult {
        for (vaddr, paddr) in pages_in(range, self.pages.size)?
            .zip(self.pages_starting_from(range.start))
        {
            pt.map(vaddr, *paddr, self.pages.size, flags)?;
        }
        Ok(())
    }

    fn clone_map(...) -> AxResult<Backend> {
        Ok(Backend::Shared(self.clone()))  // е…ұдә«зү©зҗҶйЎө
    }
}
```

#### 3.3.3 ж–Үд»¶жҳ е°„еҗҺз«Ҝ
**ж–Үд»¶**пјҡ`aspace/backend/file.rs`

ж”ҜжҢҒж–Үд»¶жҳ е°„пјҢеҢ…жӢ¬йЎөйқўзј“еӯҳе’Ңй©ұйҖҗжңәеҲ¶гҖӮ

**е…ій”®зү№жҖ§**пјҡ
- йЎөйқўзј“еӯҳйӣҶжҲҗпјҲ`CachedFile`пјү
- йЎөйқўй©ұйҖҗзӣ‘еҗ¬еҷЁ
- и„ҸйЎөж Үи®°пјҲд»…еҜ№зЈҒзӣҳж–Үд»¶пјү

```rust
pub struct FileBackendInner {
    start: VirtAddr,
    cache: CachedFile,
    flags: FileFlags,
    offset_page: u32,
    handle: AtomicUsize,
    futex_handle: Arc<()>,
}

impl FileBackendInner {
    pub fn register_listener(self: &Arc<Self>, aspace: &Arc<Mutex<AddrSpace>>) {
        let aspace = Arc::downgrade(aspace);
        let handle = self.cache.add_evict_listener({
            let this = Arc::downgrade(self);
            move |pn, _page| {
                let Some(this) = this.upgrade() else { return; };
                let Some(aspace) = aspace.upgrade() else { return; };
                let Some(mut aspace) = aspace.try_lock() else { return; };
                this.on_evict(pn, &mut aspace);
            }
        });
        self.handle.store(handle, Ordering::Release);
    }
}
```

### 3.4 ELF еҠ иҪҪеҷЁ

**ж–Үд»¶**пјҡ`mm/loader.rs`

е®һзҺ°дәҶе®Ңж•ҙзҡ„ ELF еҠ иҪҪжөҒзЁӢпјҢеҢ…жӢ¬еҠЁжҖҒй“ҫжҺҘеҷЁж”ҜжҢҒгҖӮ

**еҠ иҪҪжөҒзЁӢ**пјҡ
```rust
pub fn load_user_app(
    uspace: &mut AddrSpace,
    path: Option<&str>,
    args: &[String],
    envs: &[String],
) -> AxResult<(VirtAddr, VirtAddr)> {
    let path = path.unwrap_or("/bin/init");

    // 1. еҠ иҪҪ ELF ж–Үд»¶пјҲеёҰ LRU зј“еӯҳпјү
    let (entry, auxv) = ELF_LOADER.lock().load(uspace, path)?;

    // 2. и®ҫзҪ®з”ЁжҲ·ж Ҳ
    let stack_top = setup_user_stack(uspace, args, envs, &auxv)?;

    Ok((entry, stack_top))
}
```

**ELF зј“еӯҳжңәеҲ¶**пјҡ
```rust
