### 3.5 з”ЁжҲ·з©әй—ҙеҶ…еӯҳи®ҝй—®

**ж–Үд»¶**пјҡ`mm/access.rs`

е®һзҺ°дәҶе®үе…Ёзҡ„з”ЁжҲ·з©әй—ҙжҢҮй’Ҳи®ҝй—®пјҢеҢ…жӢ¬йЎөй”ҷиҜҜеӨ„зҗҶгҖӮ

**з”ЁжҲ·жҢҮй’Ҳзұ»еһӢ**пјҡ
```rust
#[repr(transparent)]
pub struct UserPtr<T>(*mut T);

impl<T> UserPtr<T> {
    pub fn get_as_mut(self) -> AxResult<&'static mut T> {
        check_region(self.address(), Layout::new::<T>(), Self::ACCESS_FLAGS)?;
        Ok(unsafe { &mut *self.0 })
    }

    pub fn get_as_mut_slice(self, len: usize) -> AxResult<&'static mut [T]> {
        check_region(
            self.address(),
            Layout::array::<T>(len).unwrap(),
            Self::ACCESS_FLAGS,
        )?;
        Ok(unsafe { slice::from_raw_parts_mut(self.0, len) })
    }
}
```

**еҶ…еӯҳеҢәеҹҹйӘҢиҜҒ**пјҡ
```rust
fn check_region(start: VirtAddr, layout: Layout, access_flags: MappingFlags) -> AxResult<()> {
    let align = layout.align();
    if start.as_usize() & (align - 1) != 0 {
        return Err(AxError::BadAddress);
    }

    let curr = current();
    let mut aspace = curr.as_thread().proc_data.aspace.lock();

    if !aspace.can_access_range(start, layout.size(), access_flags) {
        return Err(AxError::BadAddress);
    }

    // йў„еҲҶй…ҚйЎөйқўпјҢйҒҝе…ҚеҗҺз»ӯйЎөй”ҷиҜҜ
    let page_start = start.align_down_4k();
    let page_end = (start + layout.size()).align_up_4k();
    aspace.populate_area(page_start, page_end - page_start, access_flags)?;

    Ok(())
}
```

---

## 4. иҝӣзЁӢдёҺзәҝзЁӢз®ЎзҗҶеӯҗзі»з»ҹ

### 4.1 жһ¶жһ„жҰӮиҝ°
**ж–Үд»¶**пјҡ`src/kernel/src/task/`

иҝӣзЁӢз®ЎзҗҶеӯҗзі»з»ҹе®һзҺ°дәҶе®Ңж•ҙзҡ„ Linux е…је®№иҝӣзЁӢ/зәҝзЁӢжЁЎеһӢгҖӮ

**ж ёеҝғж•°жҚ®з»“жһ„**пјҡ
```rust
